WEBVTT

00:21.688 --> 00:24.399
<i>So, three days
and you still haven't caught him.</i>

00:25.442 --> 00:26.860
Thank you. Appreciate it.

00:27.819 --> 00:30.697
Just 'cause I don't want you here
doesn't mean I've forgotten my manners.

00:33.659 --> 00:34.660
He won't come.

00:36.078 --> 00:38.121
I brought Dale up smarter than that.

00:40.499 --> 00:45.254
What I don't get is why he escaped.
You know, my son pled guilty.

00:45.254 --> 00:47.756
I guess he figured prison
just wasn't for him.

00:48.423 --> 00:49.591
Not unusual.

00:50.884 --> 00:54.429
Bruises all over him every time I visited.

00:56.098 --> 00:59.601
Now, you wouldn't know anything
about all that, would you?

01:00.978 --> 01:04.605
Well, he does have a way
of winding people up.

01:06.859 --> 01:09.319
Why do you hate my Dale so much?

01:18.787 --> 01:21.665
I grew up in Otway. You know Otway?

01:21.665 --> 01:22.749
Yeah.

01:25.419 --> 01:26.753
My old man, he's--

01:27.754 --> 01:29.673
He wasn't the smartest fellow, I guess.

01:30.382 --> 01:31.758
Wasn't the biggest.

01:32.259 --> 01:34.928
But he worked harder than anyone. Anyone.

01:35.888 --> 01:38.265
Yeah. Dug coal for 30 years.

01:39.099 --> 01:41.977
And he was determined
that I would never go down in the ground.

01:42.686 --> 01:44.354
No, no, no, no.

01:45.022 --> 01:48.358
I was gonna have the chance
to go to university, just like your Dale.

01:49.776 --> 01:51.403
<i>Make something of myself.</i>

01:52.404 --> 01:55.365
<i>He died at barely 50,</i>

01:56.325 --> 01:58.327
<i>coughing on all the black shit
from his lungs.</i>

01:58.327 --> 02:01.663
Honest work. And it killed him.

02:02.706 --> 02:04.416
I never got to go to university.

02:07.920 --> 02:12.925
So, I hate every little prick

02:12.925 --> 02:15.719
who decides it's too hard for him.

02:15.719 --> 02:19.640
Just gonna rob people or sell junk

02:20.349 --> 02:22.726
and just piss all over
the rest of the world.

02:24.520 --> 02:25.729
Like your Dale.

02:29.525 --> 02:32.694
You know, it breaks my heart,
the thought that I'll never see him again.

02:33.862 --> 02:36.031
But I'll live without a goodbye

02:36.823 --> 02:39.117
if it means he gets to have a life

02:40.494 --> 02:42.955
away from bastards like you.

02:42.955 --> 02:44.289
You'll see him again.

02:45.165 --> 02:48.293
Right back where you saw him last time.
You can be fucking sure of that.

05:03.887 --> 05:07.224
Dr. Lin, I cannot do this.

05:07.224 --> 05:08.976
You are doctor. Not me.

05:08.976 --> 05:11.603
I'm not a doctor. I never have been.

05:11.603 --> 05:14.940
Look, you know pretty much
everything I know at this point, Parvati.

05:14.940 --> 05:17.609
He says that
he has never seen a doctor like you.

05:17.609 --> 05:19.528
You will be a great doctor for Sagar Wada,

05:19.528 --> 05:22.406
and people will come from far and wide
to consult with you.

05:22.406 --> 05:24.992
Any man should be happy
to have such a person for a wife.

05:24.992 --> 05:26.785
Be serious. This is not a joke.

05:26.785 --> 05:29.496
You're a natural, Parvati.
You're good at this.

05:29.496 --> 05:32.583
I am girl. People not listen to me--

05:32.583 --> 05:34.626
If they wanna get better, they'll have to.

05:35.544 --> 05:37.462
Prabhu and Qasim will help you.

05:42.301 --> 05:44.386
I wish you not go.

05:44.970 --> 05:48.432
You'll do fine.
-I don't just mean for the doctoring.

06:00.110 --> 06:02.154
I will need bandage now.

06:02.154 --> 06:04.364
She got you, huh? How's it feel?
-Yes, yes.

06:04.364 --> 06:06.366
I will get you. And I will get you.

06:07.576 --> 06:08.827
Joke, <i>hai</i>?

06:09.661 --> 06:11.705
Joking. Joking.

06:18.462 --> 06:19.463
Oho.

06:20.172 --> 06:23.425
Looks like your Khaderbhai
has kept his promise, huh?

06:24.259 --> 06:26.637
<i>Inshallah</i>, we will have
our own running water soon.

06:27.387 --> 06:29.264
I know you think I set you up.

06:31.308 --> 06:35.103
You did what you thought you had to do,
and I know you did it for us.

06:35.979 --> 06:37.397
But you wish I hadn't.

06:38.690 --> 06:40.817
Hungry men don't care about the past, Lin.

06:43.153 --> 06:45.864
So, is this our goodbye?

06:48.700 --> 06:51.453
Why else would you be teaching Parvati
your medicines?

06:51.453 --> 06:53.539
Or giving all your rations
to your neighbors?

06:54.122 --> 06:55.624
Yeah, I guess it is.

06:56.959 --> 07:00.087
Look, I just wanna say I know
I should have listened to you more, Qasim.

07:00.087 --> 07:04.132
Yes. You and everyone else here
because I am very wise.

07:05.801 --> 07:09.012
And you, Mr. Lin,
you are a big pain in the <i>pichhavaada</i>.

07:12.140 --> 07:13.934
I will miss you all the same.

07:27.281 --> 07:29.074
I told you, he hasn't been here.

07:30.993 --> 07:32.411
And you don't know anything?

07:34.121 --> 07:35.581
Would I be here if I did?

07:38.542 --> 07:41.712
Well, if he hasn't been back here,
then he doesn't have his passport.

07:44.548 --> 07:45.674
So, where is it, huh?

07:54.016 --> 07:55.976
I know you're fucking lying, Lisa.

08:16.205 --> 08:18.498
Move, move. I said, move, move!

08:22.211 --> 08:25.839
Hey, you can't take those. Maurizio.
-You mean this? I can't take this?

08:27.466 --> 08:28.634
No?
-Maurizio, come on.

08:28.634 --> 08:30.093
Listen to me.

08:31.845 --> 08:33.889
I can do whatever the fuck I like.

08:34.556 --> 08:35.557
Okay?

08:36.892 --> 08:40.479
You're smart, Lisa, okay?
Much smarter than him.

08:41.522 --> 08:44.107
Okay? And we can put this right.
All of us, together.

08:44.107 --> 08:47.027
You tell Modena. Okay?

08:47.778 --> 08:51.031
There's still enough time for all three
of us to leave town, but he needs--

08:52.491 --> 08:55.619
he needs to bring me that money, okay?

09:00.332 --> 09:03.460
What are we going to see, Prabhu?
I've got things to do.

09:03.460 --> 09:05.379
The future, Linbaba.

09:07.506 --> 09:08.841
It's Arun's taxi.
-No!

09:10.008 --> 09:12.261
Half the time now, it is my taxi.

09:12.261 --> 09:14.555
He cannot be driving it 24 hours
without sleep.

09:14.555 --> 09:16.640
So, when he is not driving,
I'll be driving,

09:16.640 --> 09:20.018
and he'll be taking very reasonable
percentage of my earnings.

09:20.018 --> 09:23.939
Days, I will be tour guide.
Nights, I will drive passengers.

09:23.939 --> 09:25.566
Hey!
-When do you sleep?

09:26.191 --> 09:27.484
When I'm married.

09:28.068 --> 09:31.613
Now that you are going, I will not be
making much from tour guide business.

09:32.447 --> 09:34.658
So, without you,
I'll be one of the crowd again.

09:34.658 --> 09:37.244
You'll still be,
"number one guide in Bombay."

09:40.581 --> 09:41.707
I've been thinking,

09:42.791 --> 09:45.127
when I get my papers from Didier,

09:45.127 --> 09:47.713
what do you say
you and me take that trip to your village?

09:47.713 --> 09:48.964
Meet your family.

09:49.464 --> 09:51.425
I mean, you said
it's beautiful there, right?

09:51.425 --> 09:54.720
Lin, if I go home,
my father, who's not so modern,

09:54.720 --> 09:57.139
he will hear about my courting Parvati
and want dowry.

09:57.139 --> 10:00.726
Parvati's parents, they're giving me
permission to court her,

10:00.726 --> 10:03.353
but I don't want their mind to change, <i>na</i>?

10:03.353 --> 10:05.564
And so, I want the wedding
to happen very fast.

10:05.564 --> 10:09.401
I will tell Parvati's father
I do not need a dowry. Very modern of me.

10:09.401 --> 10:12.446
He will be happy
to have modern views on this also.

10:12.988 --> 10:14.156
Yeah, I'm sure he will.

10:15.782 --> 10:18.577
You don't think
you're rushing this a little bit, mate?

10:18.577 --> 10:21.496
I mean, you and Parvati haven't really
spent that much time together.

10:21.496 --> 10:23.582
We have years for that
when we are married.

10:23.582 --> 10:27.461
Anyway, tonight is our first
official outing, Linbaba.

10:27.461 --> 10:28.795
No more sneaking.

10:30.547 --> 10:32.674
Lin, this is very tough choice for me.

10:32.674 --> 10:34.801
You are my good friend,
but Parvati, she is--

10:34.801 --> 10:36.261
No, I get it. I get it.

10:37.304 --> 10:38.847
I'm happy for you.

10:42.643 --> 10:44.144
Reynaldo's?
-Yeah.

10:45.437 --> 10:46.438
Actually, no.

10:47.814 --> 10:49.942
You know what,
I've gotta see someone else first.

10:54.738 --> 10:55.906
Who is it?

10:56.406 --> 10:58.200
I'll give you three guesses.

11:07.000 --> 11:10.504
I sat alone for two days in my hut,

11:11.922 --> 11:15.551
then I realized you weren't coming back,
so here I am.

11:17.511 --> 11:18.637
Here you are.

11:22.140 --> 11:24.226
I had something urgent to deal with.

11:25.060 --> 11:26.562
You still dealing with it?

11:26.562 --> 11:28.438
Yes, as it happens.

11:28.438 --> 11:30.524
I have responsibilities, Lin. Same as you.

11:30.524 --> 11:31.608
Not anymore.

11:33.193 --> 11:34.736
I'm leaving tomorrow.

11:36.905 --> 11:38.198
And, so we're clear,

11:39.366 --> 11:40.868
I meant what I said.

11:42.035 --> 11:45.038
And if I knew it meant
you were gonna take off and avoid me,

11:46.164 --> 11:48.792
I would still have said it.
-That's not why I left.

11:49.418 --> 11:51.336
Is it why you never came back?

11:58.468 --> 12:02.014
Anyway, I didn't wanna go
without saying goodbye.

12:03.557 --> 12:05.058
Goodbyes are important.

12:06.560 --> 12:08.187
So this is goodbye, hey?

12:10.606 --> 12:11.899
Forever.

12:14.818 --> 12:17.613
Unless you have dinner with me tonight.
-What? Jesus.

12:17.613 --> 12:19.907
It's my last night in Bombay.
Have dinner with me.

12:19.907 --> 12:22.242
Just like two normal people.

12:22.242 --> 12:25.204
You can even give me
a list of topics not to go near.

12:30.959 --> 12:32.085
I'd like that.

12:33.253 --> 12:34.838
Yeah?
-Yeah.

12:34.838 --> 12:37.799
You might need to pick a place,
'cause I don't know where to start.

12:47.726 --> 12:48.852
Keep walking.

12:49.353 --> 12:53.190
What the fuck were you thinking,
ripping off Raheem, Zhou?

12:54.233 --> 12:55.609
Maurizio tore up our place.

12:56.735 --> 12:57.903
I was scared, Sebastian.

12:57.903 --> 13:00.781
Maurizio was going to leave you behind,
so fuck him.

13:00.781 --> 13:02.115
I took it all.

13:02.115 --> 13:05.369
Lisa, we can go right now. We can--
-How?

13:05.953 --> 13:08.539
Maurizio took our passports,
so how do we get out, huh?

13:09.164 --> 13:12.918
He'll be watching for us everywhere we go.
They're gonna kill you.

13:12.918 --> 13:14.878
And they're gonna think
I was a part of it.

13:15.462 --> 13:17.464
Lisa, you wanted me to be strong.

13:17.464 --> 13:20.509
Not like this.
You should go before they hurt you.

13:20.509 --> 13:22.052
Lisa, please listen to me.

13:22.636 --> 13:25.389
Lisa, come with me. Please.

13:25.973 --> 13:27.182
I'm sorry, I can't.

13:38.569 --> 13:41.655
All those red notices and not one match.

13:42.155 --> 13:44.867
Maybe Lin Ford is just another <i>gora</i>

13:44.867 --> 13:48.287
hiding in Bombay from some bad debt
or angry wife.

13:48.287 --> 13:51.582
All the best journalists I know
have one thing in common.

13:52.082 --> 13:54.251
Total dogged persistence.

13:54.251 --> 13:55.836
Oh, they do?

13:57.629 --> 14:00.382
What? I'm not saying you don't.
-You don't think I can do it?

14:00.382 --> 14:02.009
What? You've just been humoring me?

14:02.009 --> 14:04.219
There are other things we can do
to identify him.

14:09.516 --> 14:11.810
Lin. How are you?

14:13.020 --> 14:14.104
Can't complain.

14:15.522 --> 14:17.399
I'm Lin.
-This is Nishant.

14:17.399 --> 14:20.194
He's my... boyfriend.
-I'm her friend-- boyfriend.

14:20.194 --> 14:23.030
I'm Kavita's boyfriend.
Pleasure meeting you, Lin.

14:23.739 --> 14:25.032
Yeah, likewise.

14:25.699 --> 14:27.910
I don't suppose you've seen Didier,
have you?

14:27.910 --> 14:29.786
Not for a couple of days.

14:29.786 --> 14:31.038
All right.

14:31.038 --> 14:32.623
Well, see you later.
-See you.

14:40.714 --> 14:42.424
Has Didier been here?

14:42.424 --> 14:44.676
Didier? No.

15:01.735 --> 15:03.237
Hey, it's Lin.

15:08.992 --> 15:09.993
Didier?

15:09.993 --> 15:13.330
Lin. I don't have your passport.

15:16.500 --> 15:17.501
Okay.

15:19.878 --> 15:21.505
What's going on, Didier?

15:26.385 --> 15:29.096
Look, I'm not going anywhere
until you open this door.

15:39.648 --> 15:40.649
Hi.

15:43.151 --> 15:45.362
Have you been out of here
since I last saw you?

15:45.863 --> 15:49.032
Well, one of my neighbors
is happy to bring me food and drink.

15:49.032 --> 15:51.451
I see no reason to leave.

15:55.914 --> 15:58.542
You want your photographs back
and the money to get what you need.

15:58.542 --> 16:01.879
I have both--
I have both, right-- right here.

16:01.879 --> 16:04.298
You haven't got my passport.

16:05.507 --> 16:06.592
Great.

16:50.219 --> 16:54.097
This is dangerous. Why did you come here?

16:54.097 --> 16:56.517
Didi sold my debt to this place.

16:56.517 --> 16:58.727
What could I do, tell them no?

16:59.728 --> 17:01.438
When can you leave?

17:02.898 --> 17:05.233
I'm here until my debt is paid.

17:06.234 --> 17:08.862
You shouldn't have called my office.

17:09.863 --> 17:12.074
What choice did I have?
I didn't know what else to do.

17:12.074 --> 17:13.617
I couldn't understand anything.

17:13.617 --> 17:16.036
I'm not a fool, Akash.

17:16.036 --> 17:19.455
I know our talk of running away,
our life in Canada,

17:19.455 --> 17:21.541
all that dreaming, it wasn't real.

17:21.541 --> 17:24.377
I know I could only ever be
a mistress to you.

17:24.377 --> 17:25.546
But now...

17:26.463 --> 17:32.469
I would like to see if you love me
as much as I love you.

17:32.469 --> 17:34.137
A man in my position--

17:34.137 --> 17:39.309
And it is due to this position Walidbhai
has given you big money for Sagar Wada.

17:39.309 --> 17:40.894
Use the money--

17:40.894 --> 17:43.814
Use the money you got for Sagar Wada
to set me free.

17:45.732 --> 17:47.943
If Walidbhai finds out that you are alive,

17:47.943 --> 17:49.653
his people will kill you.

17:49.653 --> 17:51.738
In either case, I will die here anyway.

17:51.738 --> 17:55.534
Still, you must never speak
of my arrangement with him.

17:55.534 --> 17:57.661
It is not safe for you.

17:59.955 --> 18:01.665
This is best for you.

18:02.749 --> 18:06.086
You, you mean. I am not safe here.

18:09.173 --> 18:12.176
Use Walid's money
to buy me from Madame Zhou.

18:13.135 --> 18:14.469
Talk to her now.

18:16.388 --> 18:19.683
And everything can be just as it was.

18:22.436 --> 18:26.523
Akash? You also want the same, right?

18:32.613 --> 18:36.116
Yes. Yes, of course.

18:39.369 --> 18:41.997
I will do what needs to be done.

18:58.013 --> 18:59.848
Minister Pandey.

19:05.479 --> 19:06.688
Please.

19:15.739 --> 19:19.368
What? Can't you just leave me to drink
and be depressed?

19:20.202 --> 19:23.997
Karla once told me depression only happens
to people who don't know how to be sad.

19:26.834 --> 19:29.127
What the-- does that even fucking mean?

19:29.127 --> 19:32.881
If Karla did less thinking
and more feeling, she'd be better off.

19:32.881 --> 19:34.800
Yeah, can't argue with that.

19:36.134 --> 19:37.302
So, what happened?

19:39.096 --> 19:40.681
Where do I begin?

19:43.225 --> 19:48.272
My father was a wonderful teacher
with one exception. Me.

19:49.606 --> 19:53.902
And my academic failures offended him
to his core.

19:56.655 --> 19:58.991
His hand,
it seemed to me when I was a child,

19:58.991 --> 20:03.328
was so large that when he struck me,
my whole body was bruised.

20:03.328 --> 20:05.289
You know, I lived in terror of those blows

20:05.289 --> 20:09.042
and the feeling of being utterly worthless
that came with it.

20:10.002 --> 20:12.129
So, at 16, I ran away.

20:12.129 --> 20:16.216
Just a young boy with his wits
and a certain degree of charm.

20:19.595 --> 20:22.764
No one has struck me like that since,
not until the other day.

20:22.764 --> 20:24.099
Those cops, it was the same.

20:24.099 --> 20:26.185
They looked at me
and saw nothing of any worth.

20:26.185 --> 20:28.187
Who gives a shit what they think?

20:28.187 --> 20:31.523
Well, they-- Deep down,
I knew they were right.

20:37.863 --> 20:39.072
What are those?

20:42.326 --> 20:43.535
Reminders.

20:45.204 --> 20:49.124
I keep them to remember
what a terrible human being I am.

20:51.335 --> 20:55.214
I had a lover when I was young. In Genova.

20:56.548 --> 20:59.510
A beautiful man inside and out.
He taught me so many things.

20:59.510 --> 21:00.761
Alberto.

21:01.929 --> 21:05.516
Wrote the most beautiful letters to me,
you know.

21:05.516 --> 21:08.894
I was born again in his arms, I think.

21:09.895 --> 21:11.813
So, what happened with Alberto?

21:12.981 --> 21:14.024
Well, he loved me.

21:17.152 --> 21:18.362
I loved him.

21:19.196 --> 21:23.116
But then he made an error of judgment.

21:23.116 --> 21:24.201
He...

21:25.244 --> 21:28.038
decided to test that love.

21:29.331 --> 21:32.960
With all his wisdom,
he didn't know that love can't be tested.

21:32.960 --> 21:36.713
Honesty, yes. Loyalty, for sure.
But not love. You know?

21:36.713 --> 21:38.882
Love goes on forever,

21:38.882 --> 21:41.301
even if we come to hate
the one we love.

21:41.301 --> 21:44.304
You can love someone
and do terrible things to them,

21:44.304 --> 21:46.223
all at the same time.

21:46.974 --> 21:48.267
So, you know,

21:50.018 --> 21:53.897
Alberto allowed me to discover
where he kept his money,

21:53.897 --> 21:57.568
so I took it all, and then-- and ran away.

21:59.236 --> 22:01.613
Love also means he'd have forgiven you.

22:04.908 --> 22:06.827
You never saw him again?

22:09.621 --> 22:11.999
Fifteen years later,
I saw him in the park,

22:13.208 --> 22:14.918
and I hurried past him.

22:15.836 --> 22:16.837
I--

22:18.422 --> 22:21.675
I hurried past that good and brilliant man
who loved me,

22:21.675 --> 22:24.511
simply because he was old
and no longer beautiful.

22:28.265 --> 22:31.268
His weakness, his loneliness,
they terrified me.

22:31.810 --> 22:33.645
I didn't want to be part of it.

22:35.147 --> 22:39.234
And now... now I am him.

22:40.819 --> 22:44.364
When I was in that jail being beaten,
I was back with my father.

22:44.364 --> 22:45.991
Worthless, useless.

22:45.991 --> 22:50.954
It was as if my whole life
has been a mirage.

22:53.665 --> 22:55.834
Only if you stay in this mess.

22:55.834 --> 22:58.086
Whatever you're running from,
you already escaped.

22:58.086 --> 22:59.296
Those cops, they're here.

22:59.296 --> 23:01.381
Every time I walk the street,
it'll be in fear.

23:05.302 --> 23:06.929
I'm a bank robber, Didier.

23:08.639 --> 23:10.140
I escaped jail.

23:11.141 --> 23:13.519
I'm one of the most wanted men
in Australia.

23:15.896 --> 23:18.732
The cop who put me away,
he'd happily see me dead.

23:18.732 --> 23:23.779
Why tell me? Is this like a test?
You know, I fail tests.

23:23.779 --> 23:25.280
No, it's no test.

23:26.448 --> 23:28.450
I just want you to know I understand.

23:29.535 --> 23:32.538
I wake up every day
and I still think they're coming for me.

23:33.914 --> 23:36.667
The fear doesn't go away,
whether you stay in here or not.

23:39.378 --> 23:40.838
But every day we're free

23:42.005 --> 23:44.591
is a kick in the balls to those bastards.

23:58.647 --> 23:59.690
Barry,

24:00.983 --> 24:02.860
you know I don't like bad news.

24:09.908 --> 24:12.369
It's a match. Today's the day, Sarge.

